Phrases	
Thank you (to one)  Fá'po ̪etho'páxve thá / Fá'po 	Fá'po ̪etho'páxve thá / Fá'po 
    lit. May the Exalted Revered-God love you / May-love	
Thank you (to more than one)	Fá'po ̪etho'páxve há / Fá'po 
    lit. May the Exalted Revered-God love you / May-love	
Your are welcome	háx thwá
    lit. And back (meaning to the thank-er)	
please (to 1)	etho'thá
    lit. Exalted-you	
please (to many)	etho'há
    lit. Exalted-you	
hello	gáx káth
    lit. from the sea	
bye	pe káth
    lit. to the sea	
sorry (to one)   thá'hix ñáf thá
    lit. I pray for you
sorry (to many)   thá'hix ñáf há
    lit. I pray for you
Bye   yoth yámtuux
    lit. Calm seas (to you) forever
welcome!   nithbix
    lit. of home
	
